  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-child-friendly-restaurants$gb$, $gb$Cape Town Child-Friendly Restaurants$gb$, $gb$Child Friendly Eating$gb$, $gb$<p><br /></p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://www.capetourism.com/restaurants-with-a-play-area/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/42qahqkScO0RJQtNQx7x$gb$, -33.922087, 18.4231418),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-markets$gb$, $gb$Cape Town Markets$gb$, $gb$shopping$gb$, $gb$<p><br /></p><ul><li><br /></li><li><a href="http://www.neighbourgoodsmarket.co.za/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>The Neighbourgoods Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://waterfrontfoodmarket.com/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>V & A Food Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="https://lourensfordexperiences.co.za/fete/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Lourensford Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/vegangoodsmarket/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Vegan Goods Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.mojomarket.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Mojo Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.elginrailwaymarket.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Elgin Railway Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><strong style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><u>The </u></strong><a href="http://www.theoldbiscuitmill.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong><u>Old Biscuit Mill</u></strong></a></li></ul><p>(<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">373-375 Albert Road, Woodstock, </span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">7915)</span></p><p>A vibrant, warm-hearted little village in the heart of Woodstock; where talented people come together to share, collaborate and show off their heartfelt passion. The Mill is home to day and night markets, delicious food stalls, designer stores, decadent restaurants; as well as an inspiring line up of festivals and productions. You can visit T<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">he Neighbourgoods Market on Saturdays.</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Fridays (10:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.) & </span>Saturdays - (9:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://www.ozcf.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Oranjezicht City Farm Market</strong></a></li></ul><p>(<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Granger Bay Boulevard, V&A Waterfront, 8051)</span></p><p>Despite the name, this local farmer’s market is actually located under tents and trees in the Granger Bay section of the V&A Waterfront. Boasting stunning sea views and a range of fresh produce; the market celebrates local food, culture and community in support of the educational mission of the nonprofit Oranjezicht City Farm. It’s a wonderfully relaxing place to do your weekly grocery shopping. You’ll find fresh-from-the-patch veggies and herbs, fruit, bread, organic dairy products, free-range eggs, raw honey, muesli and ethically sourced meats and seafood. There’s a wonderful array of artisanal food stalls selling amazing cooked and raw dishes for all palates and preferences - from carnivores to vegan; chocoholics to diabetics. There’s plenty of outdoor seating and space for the kids. This market is also dog-friendly.</p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Saturdays (8:30 a.m. - 2:00 p.m.) & Sundays (8:30 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://cpv.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>Cape Point Vineyards Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(Silvermine Road, Noordhoek, 7979)</span></p><p>A must-see event for Peninsula locals, after-work city folk and tourists alike. This weekly pop-up market takes place at the Cape Point Vineyards Restaurant & Function Venue; an idyllic lakeside setting overlooking scenic vineyards, Noordhoek’s mountain range and the nearby ocean. This vibrant market, boasts a selection of the country’s most iconic food vendors such as <strong>Peter Goffe-Wood’s </strong>"<strong>Kitchen Cowboys</strong>" and "<strong>The Lamb Man</strong>". Also featuring fantastic foods, are rising stars "<strong>Sunshine Food Co.</strong>" with amazing veggie burgers and "<strong>Something Simple</strong>" with vegan sushi. All these decadent foods can, of course, be washed down with Cape Point Vineyards’ award winning wine collection; alongside a variety of craft beer.</p><ul><li>Thursdays <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(4:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://www.thefarmvillage.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>The Farm Village Market</strong></a></li></ul><p>(<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Noordhoek Main Road, Goedehoop Estate, 7979)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">A small market held at the Noordhoek Farm Village. Choose between Italian, pottjiekos, Mexican, vegan and many more. </span>The market is held under a tent (with gas heaters) but is weather-dependent. If in doubt, <span style="color: black;">please contact organisers to confirm.</span></p><ul><li>Wednesdays <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(4:00 p.m. - 8:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://www.therange.co.za/food-market.html" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong>The Range Market</strong></a></li></ul><p><strong>(</strong><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Orpen Road, Tokai, 7966)</span></p><p>The most incredible views and a wide variety of food options from pizza, stir-fry and croquettes; to Greek, Mexican, Dutch and Chinese. They have a sweet selection of Belgian waffles, cr<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">ê</span>pes and cakes; plus a tantalising home-made liquor, local wines from the valley and craft beer on tap. They offer a children’s programme and a safe, fun place for them to play. There is no entrance fee and ample secure parking bays available. Housed inside a massive marquee, offering seating inside or outside for all weather conditions.</p><ul><li>Fridays <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(4:30 p.m. - 9:30 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.bayharbour.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong><u>Bay Harbour Market</u></strong></a></li></ul><p><strong style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);"><u>﻿</u>(</strong><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">31 Harbour Road, Hout Bay, 7872)</span></p><p>Located at the edge of the sea, overlooking Chapman’s Peak; this once-abandoned factory is now the legendary Bay Harbour Market, attracting some twenty-four thousand visitors each month. An inspiring destination for breakfast, lunch and dinner. This weekend market kicks off with <strong>Friday Nite LIVE!</strong> which offers live music. There are at least twenty-six culinary experts catering to everything from Tunisian cuisine, seafood platters, gourmet sandwiches, wood-fired pizza and everything in-between.</p><ul><li>Fridays <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(5:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m.) & </span>Saturdays - Sundays <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(9:30 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/markets/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/DfBeE2TMSLyieHxH5Fou$gb$, -33.9248685, 18.424055299999964),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-spa-s$gb$, $gb$Cape Town Spa's$gb$, $gb$Health & Wellness$gb$, $gb$<p>Cape Town Spa's</p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://www.timeout.com/cape-town/things-to-do/best-spa-cape-town$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/dE79mXOThS66X6a5rzvM$gb$, -33.922087, 18.4231418),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-steakhouses$gb$, $gb$Cape Town Steakhouses$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p>Cape Town's Best Steakhouses</p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://www.capetourism.com/steak-restaurants-cape-town/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/JEYuD3ROT6xLKthKYyqH$gb$, -33.922087, 18.4231418),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-tidal-pools$gb$, $gb$Cape Town Tidal Pools$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<p>Cape Town Tidal Pools</p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/tidal-pools/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/J46EW6N2Td6W484FPDMT$gb$, -33.922087, 18.4231418),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-s-best-beaches$gb$, $gb$Cape Town's Best Beaches$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Clifton 4th Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">One of Cape Town's most popular beaches, it consists of four separate beach coves (Clifton 1st - 4th). They are all well-protected from the wind and you are able to hire loungers and beach umbrellas here. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Camps Bay Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">A beautiful, albeit crowded beach alongside a strip of trendy restaurants and cocktail bars.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Llandudno Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">A</span><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"> </strong><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">stunning beach with breathtaking sunsets. It never gets too crowded, though parking is minimal. Best to arrive early. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Noordhoek Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">An impressive beach, stretching over 8km. It is perfect for long walks along the coast.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Muizenberg Beach</u> </strong><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">(Also known as Surfer's Corner)</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">Is the best place for surfing and learning how to surf. There are also a number of restaurants and cafés nearby.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>St. James Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">Is a small, quaint beach. It is well-sheltered from the wind and has a tidal pool that is perfect for children.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Fish Hoek Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">Is one of the safest and cleanest beaches in Cape Town. The currents are gentle for relaxed swimming and you may even spot a few whales.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);"><u>Boulders Beach</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(57, 57, 57);">Located in Simons Town and protected from the wind and large waves by ancient granite boulders. It is home to the only colony of African penguins in the world. They are classified as an endangered species, with around three thousand remaining. As this is a Nature Reserve, there is a small entrance fee to gain access.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><u>Fisherman's Beach and </u></strong><strong style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);"><u>Seaforth Beach</u></strong></p><p>Also located in Simons Town, with the warmer Indian Ocean waters, these two beaches make for a great place to swim, kayak and body-board. They are surrounded by grassy lawns which is perfect for picnics.</p>$gb$, $gb$Llandudno, Cape Town, 7806, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/best-beaches/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/RDX8WxyGQ12wAjEmA5jd$gb$, -34.0099528, 18.34304750000001),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-town-s-top-restaurants$gb$, $gb$Cape Town's Top Restaurants$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p><br /></p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/best-restaurants$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/rwtPYgRTAOdovI8Rb1gG$gb$, -33.9248685, 18.424055299999964),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-cape-xtreme-adventure-tours-and-cape-to-addo-safaris$gb$, $gb$Cape Xtreme Adventure Tours and Cape to Addo Safaris$gb$, $gb$activities$gb$, $gb$<p>Book your Adventure tours with an experienced company</p>$gb$, $gb$Unit C3, Maitland Business Park, 733 Voortrekker Rd, Maitland, Cape Town, 7405, South Africa$gb$, $gb$+27 76 016 9696$gb$, $gb$https://www.capextreme.com/contact-us/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/1uohivlQcqvPBFrLvm7x$gb$, -33.9176009, 18.5156664),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-castle-of-good-hope$gb$, $gb$Castle of Good Hope$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<p>https://www.castleofgoodhope.co.za/</p>$gb$, $gb$Darling St, Buitenkant St, &, Cape Town, 8001, South Africa$gb$, $gb$012 461 4673$gb$, $gb$http://www.castleofgoodhope.co.za/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/LNiQZZPzTYqhxp4yO3lV$gb$, -33.926046, 18.42805809999999),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-chavonnes-battery-museum$gb$, $gb$Chavonnes Battery Museum$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<p>The Chavonnes Battery was a fortification protecting Cape Town, South Africa, built in the early 18th century. It is now a museum and function venue.</p>$gb$, $gb$Clock Tower Precinct, Victoria & Alfred Waterfront, Cape Town, 8001, South Africa$gb$, $gb$021 416 6230$gb$, $gb$http://www.chavonnesbattery.co.za/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/UnYkWxgSNO40PpOWP45V$gb$, -33.907055, 18.421593),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-chefs-warehouse-at-tintswalo-atlantic$gb$, $gb$Chefs Warehouse at Tintswalo Atlantic$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p>Sitting at the foot of Chapman's Peak, Chefs Warehouse at Tintswalo Atlantic is a sea-side culinary dream. </p>$gb$, $gb$W9M9+W5, Hout Bay, Cape Town, 7979, South Africa$gb$, $gb$021 541 0165$gb$, $gb$https://www.chefswarehouse.co.za/cw-tintswalo$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/7Vk59gHkTPqXbIlB75J7$gb$, -34.06518749999999, 18.3679375),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-child-friendly-restaurants$gb$, $gb$Child-friendly Restaurants$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="http://www.colcacchio.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Col'Cacchio</strong></a></p><p>An Italian restaurant chain that serves pizza, pasta and salads. There is a great children’s play area and the kids are given dough to bake in the ovens.</p><p>&gt; <a href="https://www.google.co.za/search?q=(Unit%2011%2C%20Park%20%27n%20Shop%20Centre%2C%20Firgrove%20Way%2C%20Meadowridge%2C%207806)&rlz=1C1GGRV_enZA804ZA805&oq=(Unit+11%2C+Park+%27n+Shop+Centre%2C+Firgrove+Way%2C+Meadowridge%2C+7806)&aqs=chrome..69i57&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8&npsic=0&rflfq=1&rlha=0&rllag=-34040119,18456490,18&tbm=lcl&rldimm=10816460286084579180&lqi=Cj8oVW5pdCAxMSwgUGFyayAnbiBTaG9wIENlbnRyZSwgRmlyZ3JvdmUgV2F5LCBNZWFkb3dyaWRnZSwgNzgwNikiA4gBAVocChp1bml0IDExIHBhcmsgbiBzaG9wIGNlbnRyZQ&ved=2ahUKEwiG_PLGvefeAhWLzYUKHfzyA3kQvS4wAXoECAAQIg&rldoc=1&tbs=lrf:!2m4!1e17!4m2!17m1!1e2!2m1!1e3!2m1!1e16!3sIAE,lf:1,lf_ui:4#rlfi=hd:;si:10816460286084579180,l,Cj8oVW5pdCAxMSwgUGFyayAnbiBTaG9wIENlbnRyZSwgRmlyZ3JvdmUgV2F5LCBNZWFkb3dyaWRnZSwgNzgwNikiA4gBAVocChp1bml0IDExIHBhcmsgbiBzaG9wIGNlbnRyZQ;mv:!1m2!1d-34.0396389!2d18.4567099!2m2!1d-34.0406306!2d18.4555361;tbs:lrf:!2m1!1e3!2m1!1e16!2m4!1e17!4m2!17m1!1e2!3sIAE,lf:1,lf_ui:4" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><u>Meadowridge</u></a><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);"> (+27 21 712 3190)</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (8:30 a.m. - 10:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.grootconstantia.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Groot Constantia</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Groot Constantia Wine Estate, Groot Constantia Road, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">There are two child-friendly restaurants here; Simon's Restaurant and Jonkerhuis. They are wonderful for kids as they have beautiful, spacious gardens where kids are free to run around.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">&gt; </span><a href="http://www.simons.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u>Simon's Restaurant</u></a><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"> </span>(+27 21 794 1143)</p><ul><li>Mondays - Fridays (11:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</li><li>Saturdays & Sundays (11:00 a.m. - 9:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p>&gt; <a href="http://www.jonkershuisconstantia.co.za/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">Jonkershuis</a><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;"> </span>(+27 21 794 6255)</p><ul><li>Mondays - Saturdays (9:00 a.m. - 9:00 p.m.)</li><li>Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://blockhousekitchen.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Blockhouse Kitchen</u></strong></a></p><p>(Spaanschemat River Road, Fir Grove, Constantia, 7806)</p><p>+27 21 794 3010 //<u> </u><a href="mailto:info@bhkitchen.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u>info@bhkitchen.co.za</u></a></p><p><span style="background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">An all-day dining experience, with a strong focus on wholesome and healthy food.They are a child-friendly establishment, with a large variety of kiddie's foods to choose from.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 11:30 a.m.) - Breakfast</li><li>Mondays & Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 5:00 p.m.) - Lunch & Dinner</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (12:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.) - Lunch & Dinner</li></ul>$gb$, $gb$Constantia, Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://www.capetourism.com/restaurants-with-a-play-area/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/fY4oIRsQNueI9JVcnq39$gb$, -34.0257608, 18.423078900000064),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-constantia-dining-caf-s$gb$, $gb$Constantia Dining Cafés$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="https://www.labellecampsbay.co.za/our-restaurant-constantia-location" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>la Belle</u></strong></a><strong style="color: black;"><u> Bistro & Bakery</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Alphen Boutique Hotel, Alphen Drive, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>+27 21 795 6336 // <a href="mailto:labelle@alphen.co.za.%20It" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">labelle@alphen.co.za</a></p><p>Great places for breakfast or casual lunches with freshly baked quiches, gourmet burgers, delicious cupcakes or chocolate torte. Enjoy juices or fruity cocktails straight <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">from the orchards.</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (7:00 a.m. - 11:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.chardonnaydeli.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Chardonnay Deli</strong></a></p><p>(87 Constantia Main Road, Constantia, 7806)</p><p><strong>﻿</strong><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">+27 21 795 0606</span><strong> // </strong><a href="mailto:info@chardonnaydeli.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">info@chardonnaydeli.co.za</a><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);"> </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(81, 81, 80);">An upmarket farm stall that serves light meals. It's set in the beautiful Constantia Valley. You will be able to find a variety of healthy and homemade products, in a relaxed, stylish venue that is steeped in history.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (7:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.fourandtwentycafe.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Four & Twenty Café</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(23 Wolfe Street, Wynberg, 7800)</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">+27 21 762 0975 // </span><a href="mailto:info@fourandtwentycafe.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">info@fourandtwentycafe.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">A tiny spot with ornate couches, teacup light fittings and the most delicious breakfast and lunch menu. They get quite busy and only take reservations for five or more people; best to arrive and know that the wait will be worth it. It's situated j</span>ust on the other side of Constantia in Wynberg’s Chelsea Village.</p><ul><li>Mondays - Saturdays (8:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</li><li>Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.peddlars.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Peddlars</u></strong></a><strong style="color: black;"><u> & Co.</u></strong></p><p>(32 Spaanschemat River Road, Constantia, 7806)</p><p>+27 21 794 7747 // <a href="mailto:letsmeet@peddlars.co.za" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">letsmeet@peddlars.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">They serve pub food and offer a range of dining experiences </span>which comprise of:</p><p><u>Bold by Brad Ball</u> - Interesting, sometimes surprising dishes in a casual setting. It offers alluring cocktails and exceptional wines. </p><p><u>Graciales</u> - Small plates of deliciousness, perfect for sharing with friends and family. The wine list focuses on the Constantia Valley Estates.</p><p><u>The Oak Terrace</u> - A great place to dine alfresco under oak trees and sample fabulous wines and delicious pastas, salads and burgers. </p><p><u>The Local</u> - A great pub with great grub, serving up some of the Cape’s finest craft beers.</p><p><u style="color: black;">Volaré Ristorante</u><span style="color: black;"> - Smaller but very trendy, this restaurant offers scrumptious Italian cuisine and a relaxed atmosphere.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://incognitobar.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Incognito Bar</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Alphen Drive, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>+27 21 795 6300 // <a href="mailto:info@incognitobar.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">info@incognitobar.co.za</a></p><p>The newest addition, Incognito is an upbeat cocktail lounge with exceptional views of the lush gardens at The Alphen. Relax and enjoy a curated food and drink offering. A selection of signature cocktails, local wines and artisanal spirits make Incognito the ideal drinks venue.</p><ul><li>Mondays - Fridays (4:00 p.m. - 12:00 a.m.)</li><li>Saturdays (12:00 p.m. - 12:00 a.m.)</li><li>Sundays & Public Holidays (12:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Tasha’s </strong></p><p>Great place for a weekend breakfast, lunch or brunch. Big space inside and on the terrace. Plenty of healthy options to choose from.</p><p>Constantia Village Shopping Centre - Spaanschemacht Road +27 81 028 0528</p><p>Mon to Sun - 8:00 - 18:00</p><p>Great place for a weekend breakfast, lunch or brunch. Big space inside and on the terrace. Plenty of healthy options to choose from.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Spirit Cafe</strong></p><p>Great tasty and seasonal food that suits vegan and vegetarian diets as well as those that have specific nutritional requirements.</p><p>Shop 10A, Constantia Village, Constantia, Cape Town</p><p>+21 (0)21 795 0167</p><p>Mon - Fri: 08:00 - 16:30</p><p>Sat: 08:00 - 14:00</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Wild Sprout </strong></p><p>﻿A heath focused restaurant and grocer in Cape Town, offering an increasing large range of vegan, gluten free and healthy food and goods</p><p>Constantia Village Courtyard, Constantia, Cape Town, 7708</p><p><strong>Phone: </strong>068 605 7318</p><p><strong>Menu: </strong>wsprout.co.za</p>$gb$, $gb$Constantia, Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, null, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/rzLeJbGFS9MeYFO3zw8M$gb$, -34.0257608, 18.423078900000064),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-constantia-restaurants$gb$, $gb$Constantia Restaurants$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="https://www.greenhouserestaurant.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Greenhouse Restaurant</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">(The Hohenort Hotel, </span><span style="color: inherit;">93 Brommersvlei Road, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 795 6226 // </span><a href="mailto:eat@greenhouserestaurant.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">eat@greenhouserestaurant.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">This multi-award winning restaurant offers a modern South African dining experience and is ranked as one of the country's top ten restaurants.</span></p><ul><li>Fridays & Saturdays (12:00 p.m. - 2:00 p.m.) - Lunch</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (6:00 p.m. - 9:30 p.m.) - Dinner</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://95atparks.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>95 at Parks</u></strong></a></p><p>(114 Constantia Main Road, Constantia, 7806)</p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 761 0247 // </span><a href="mailto:parks@95keerom.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">parks@95keerom.com</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Award wining Italian restaurant that features a bar, sunny conservatory, private dining room and small outdoor area overlooking the cottage garden.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Saturdays (12:00 p.m. - 3:00 p.m. & 6:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.lacolombe.co.za/menus" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>La Colombe Restaurant</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Silvermist Wine Estate, Main Road, Constantia Nek, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 794 2390 // </span><a href="mailto:reservations@lacolombe.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black;">r</a><a href="mailto:reservations@lacolombe.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(84, 84, 84);">eservations@lacolombe.co.za</a></p><p>La Colombe has consistently received world-wide acclaim and is positioned amongst the top restaurants in the world. <span style="color: black;">It’s a special treat to experience not only the food but also the restaurant’s colonial charm. Since they are a fine dining establishment, they do not admit children under the age of ten years old.</span></p><p><u>*Booking is absolutely essential as they are often booked up weeks in advance.</u></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 2:00 p.m. & 6:30 p.m. - 9:00 p.m)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://laparada.co.za/constantia-nek/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>La Parada</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(84, 84, 84);">(1 Hout Bay Road, Constantia Nek, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>+27 21795 0620 // <a href="mailto:constantianek@laparada.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(84, 84, 84); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">constantianek@laparada.co.za</a></p><p>With beautiful sea views and a delicious menu of Spanish tapas and cocktails; this Spanish restaurant makes for a wonderful dining experience.</p><ul><li>Mondays - Fridays (9:00 a.m. - 11:00 p.m.)</li><li>Saturdays & Sundays (8:00 a.m. - 12:00 a.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.foxcroft.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Foxcroft Restaurant</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Unit 8, High Constantia Centre, Groot Constantia Road, Constantia)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 202 3304 // </span><a href="mailto:reservations@foxcroft.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">reservations@foxcroft.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Foxcroft, a fairly recent restaurant, could be considered the shiniest jewel of the High Constantia Centre. With a menu of such delicious foods to tantalize your taste buds, you will be returning again and again. The outside terrace is lively, offering al fresco dining with stunning views of the surrounding mountains and the inside </span>décor gives it a <span style="color: black;">warm and cosy ambience.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 2:00 p.m. & 6:00 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.jakes.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Jakes in the Village</u></strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(A5, Steenberg Village Centre, Steenberg Road, Westlake, 7945)</span></p><p>+27 21 701 3272 // <a href="mailto:tokai@jakes.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">tokai@jakes.co.za</a></p><p>Nestled beneath the Constantiaberg Mountains and alongside Steenberg Golf Estate, Jakes is an incredible place to socialize, while enjoying creatively designed meals and an extensive wine list.</p><ul><li>Mondays - Saturdays (11:30 p.m. - 12:00 a.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong style="color: black;"><u>Bl</u></strong><a href="https://www.blanko.co.za/menu" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>anko</u></strong></a><strong style="color: black;"><u>.</u></strong></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Alphen Boutique Hotel, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>+27 21 795 6313 // manager<a href="mailto:manager@blanko.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">@blanko.co.za</a></p><p>This restaurant is one of three places to eat at The Alphen Hotel. They have a modern Italian themed menu, with a diverse offering from antipasti to insalata, pesce, pasta, carne, dolci and zuppe.</p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 12:00 a.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.chefswarehouse.co.za/beau-constantia" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Chefs Warehouse Beau Constantia</u></strong></a></p><p>(Constantia Main Road, Glen Alpine, Constantia, 7806)</p><p><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">+27 21 794 8632</span> // <a href="mailto:info@chefswarehouse.co.za" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">info@chefswarehouse.co.za</a></p><p>A casual fine-dining experience. Local produce, partly grown on their farm, and their menus change regularly. You can expect fusion flavours from South Africa with Thai and Vietnamese. <span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">They also have an amazing selection of wines to choose from. Reservations are recommended.</span></p><ul><li>Tuesdays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 2:30 p.m.) - Lunch</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (5:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.) - Dinner</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://blockhousekitchen.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong><u>Blockhouse Kitchen</u></strong></a></p><p>(Spaanschemat River Road, Fir Grove, Constantia, 7806)</p><p>+27 21 794 3010 // <a href="mailto:info@bhkitchen.co.za" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">info@bhkitchen.co.za</a></p><p><span style="background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">An all-day dining experience, with a strong focus on wholesome and healthy food. They work with sustainable food and follow ethical practices, like using the whole animal and vegetable. A positive effect in the environment, and allows them to be very generous in portion sizes and pricing.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 11:30 a.m.) - Breakfast</li><li>Mondays & Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 5:00 p.m.) - Lunch & Dinner</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (12:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.) - Lunch & Dinner</li></ul>$gb$, $gb$Constantia, Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/constantia-restaurants$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/HN5aALwDSVqGZTBmbt1r$gb$, -34.0257608, 18.423078900000064),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-constantia-wine-farms$gb$, $gb$Constantia Wine Farms$gb$, $gb$activities$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="http://www.grootconstantia.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Groot Constantia</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: black;">(Groot Constantia Road, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>+27 21 794 1143 // <a href="mailto:enquiries@grootconstantia.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">enquiries@grootconstantia.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Is only one of many great wine farms in the area, but it has to be visited for its beautiful grounds, delicious wines, and the </span><a href="https://www.iziko.org.za/museums/groot-constantia-manor-house" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Groot Constantia Manor House</strong></a><span style="color: black;">, a museum that epitomizes Cape Dutch architecture and that of a nineteenth-century home.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">Have a great meal at </span><a href="http://www.simons.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Simon’s</strong></a><strong style="color: black;"> </strong><span style="color: black;">or</span><strong style="color: black;"> </strong><a href="http://jonkershuisconstantia.co.za.www35.jnb2.host-h.net/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Jonkershuis Restaurant</strong></a><strong style="color: black;"> </strong><span style="color: black;">and</span><strong style="color: black;"> </strong><span style="color: black;">d</span>on’t forget to visit the ducks!</p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 5:30 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.kleinconstantia.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Klein Constantia</strong></a></p><p>(37 Klein Constantia Road, Nova Constantia, 7806)</p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 794 5188 // </span><a href="mailto:info@kleinconstantia.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@kleinconstantia.com</a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Dating back to 1865 and described as one of the world’s most beautiful wine estates, Klein Constantia is set amidst ancient trees on the upper foothills of the Constantiaberg, with views across False Bay.</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (10:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.buitenverwachting.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Buitenverwachting</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(37 Klein Constantia Road, Nova Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p>Beyond Restaurant 021 794 0306<span style="color: black;"> // </span>https://beyondrestaurant.co.za/make-a-booking/</p><p>Peter Tempelhoff’s enduring food philosophy is one that centres on provenance – a philosophy than ensures that the concept never eclipses the importance of the ingredients. At beyond, special attention has been paid to sourcing a diverse range of special raw produce.</p><p><strong>OPENING TIMES</strong></p><p>Monday & Tuesday: Closed</p><p>Lunch – 12:00 to 14:30</p><p>Wednesday to Sunday</p><p>Dinner – 18:00 to 20:30</p><p>Wednesday to Saturday</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Coffee BloC Restaurant</strong></p><p>The perfect destination to unwind, work or socialise while indulging in exceptional coffee and delicious food. Our cozy neighbourhood-style café offers a welcoming and comfortable space, allowing you to escape the pressures of everyday life and find cheer in the company of great food and friendly faces.</p><p>Tel: 021 794 5190/1</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.beauconstantia.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Beau Constantia</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(1043 Constantia Main Road, Glen Alpine, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 794 8632 // </span><a href="mailto:reservations@beauconstantia.com" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">reservations@beauconstantia.</a><a href="mailto:restaurant@buitenwachting.com" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">com</a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(74, 74, 74);">Beau Constantia is a boutique wine farm situated very high up on the Constantia Mountains, where meticulous attention to detail in the vineyard leads to distinctive handcrafted wines. </span><a href="http://www.chefswarehouse.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Chef's Warehouse</strong></a><strong style="color: black;"> </strong><span style="color: black;">restaurant is a must-visit for great food.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">*</span><u style="color: black;">Booking in advance is essential.</u></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Tuesdays - Sundays (11:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://eaglesnestwines.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Eagles' Nest</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Constantia Main Rd, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 794 4095 // </span><a href="mailto:info@eaglesnestwines.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@eaglesnestwines.com</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Nestled at the foot of the awe inspiring Table Mountain, this pristine and boutique family-owned vineyard has in recent years gained a striking reputation for both its beauty and award winning wines.</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (10:00 a.m. - 4:30 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.steenbergfarm.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Steenberg Farm</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: black;">(</span>Steenberg Estate, Steenberg Road, Constantia Valley, 7945)</p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 713 2222 // </span><a href="mailto:info@steenberghotel.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@steenberghotel.com</a></p><p>A very popular spot for a smart lunch or dinner is <a href="https://www.steenbergfarm.com/bistro1682/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Bistro Sixteen82</strong></a><strong style="color: black;"> </strong>at the Steenberg Hotel. The walls are covered with bottles of wines and the ceiling is interestingly covered with perfectly intertwined wooden branches. Make your way through their amazing tapas menu and their delicious desserts.</p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (10:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Tryn</p><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.constantiaglen.com/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Constantia Glen</strong></a></p><p>(<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Constantia Main Road, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">+27 21 795 5639 // </span><a href="mailto:reservations@constantiaglen.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">reservations@constantiaglen.com</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Constantia Glen is ideally located below Constantia Nek, a picturesque boutique wine estate; producing ultra-premium, cool climate wines. </span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Sundays - Fridays (10:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m.)</span></li><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Saturdays (10:00 a.m. - 8:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://uitsig.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Constantia Uitsig Estate</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(ERF12995 Spaanschemat River Road, Fir Grove, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">+27 21 794 3010 // </span><a href="mailto:info@uitsig.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">info@uitsig.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">They have a fine dining restaurant (</span><a href="http://opendoorrestaurant.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>The Open Door</strong></a><span style="color: black;">), as well as a Chocolate Shop, Ice-cream Shop, Sushi Box, and a Beer and Wine Shop.</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Saturdays (9:00 a.m. - 9:30 p.m.)</span></li><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Sundays (9:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul>$gb$, $gb$Constantia, Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, $gb$https://constantiawineroute.com/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/kPajgsR0QamlztoEbVL6$gb$, -34.0257608, 18.4230789),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-district-six-museum$gb$, $gb$District Six Museum$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<p>Currently, the apartheid museum serves as a remembrance of the once lively multi-racial area that was forcefully removed during apartheid in the 1960s and 1970s.</p>$gb$, $gb$25A Buitenkant St, District Six, Cape Town, 8000, South Africa$gb$, $gb$021 466 7200$gb$, $gb$http://www.districtsix.co.za/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/OuA9ZBj5Rwc0ye9Sgbkx$gb$, -33.9277222, 18.423677),
