  ($gb$montroseterrace-noordhoek-s-highlights$gb$, $gb$Noordhoek's Highlights$gb$, $gb$Places to eat$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="http://cpv.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Cape Point Vineyards</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Silvermine Road, Noordhoek, 7985)</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">+27 21 789 0900 // </span><a href="mailto:info@cape-point.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@cape-point.co</a><a href="mailto:info@capepoint.com" target="_blank" style="color: black;">m</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Can be visited for wine tasting and lunches. They hold a market every Thursday evening and they have a fine dining restaurant that boasts the most exquisite views of Noordhoek Beach. Picnics can be ordered and enjoyed at this beautiful estate.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Saturdays (8:30 a.m. - 8:30 p.m.)</li><li>Sundays (8:30 a.m. - 6:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.caferoux.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Café Roux</strong></a></p><p>(Corner Village Lane & Noordhoek Main Road, Noordhoek, 7979)</p><p>+27 21 789 2538 // <a href="mailto:info@caferoux.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@caferoux.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">Located in Noordhoek Farm Village; they have great food, a kids' menu, a jungle-gym and play area, and various children's activities.</span></p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (8:30 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</li><li>Wednesdays - Saturdays (6:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m.)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.thefoodbarn.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>The Foodbarn</strong></a></p><p>(Corner Village Lane & Noordhoek Main Road, Noordhoek, 7979)</p><p><span style="color: black;">Has two restaurants - the more formal restaurant, and the deli. The restaurant serves delicious and decadent fine dining. The Deli, during the day, offers fresh bread and the greatest coffee; while at night, transforms into a vibey tapas bar.</span></p><p>&gt; <a href="https://www.thefoodbarn.co.za/restaurant/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;"><strong>Foodbarn Restaurant</strong></a><strong> </strong>(+27 21 789 1390)</p><ul><li>Mondays - Sundays (12:00 p.m. - 2:30 p.m.) - Lunch</li><li>Wednesdays - Saturdays (7:00 p.m. - 9:30 p.m.) - Dinner</li></ul><p>&gt; <a href="https://www.thefoodbarn.co.za/deli/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;"><strong>Deli</strong></a><strong style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;"> </strong><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;">(</span>+27 21 789 1966)</p><ul><li>Sundays & Mondays (8:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.)</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (8:00 a.m. - 9:00 p.m.)</li><li>Tuesdays - Saturdays (6:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m.) - Tapas Bar</li></ul>$gb$, $gb$Noordhoek, Cape Town, 7979, South Africa$gb$, null, null, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/gRkHgTbYS1KaqwzD2iP0$gb$, -34.0947539, 18.394966100000033),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-norval-foundation-art-museum$gb$, $gb$Norval Foundation Art Museum$gb$, $gb$attractions$gb$, $gb$<h3><strong><u>Contact Details for Norval Foundation:</u></strong></h3><p><br /></p><p>Cell: +27 87 654 5900</p><p>Email: <a href="mailto:info@norvalfoundation.org" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: black;"><strong>info@norvalfoundation.org</strong></a></p><p>Address:<a href="https://www.google.co.za/maps/place/Norval+Foundation/@-34.0765258,18.4265338,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x1dcc41e2b6cade59:0x7d001e7f80e9aeb1!8m2!3d-34.0765258!4d18.4287225" target="_blank"> </a><a href="https://www.google.co.za/maps/place/Norval+Foundation/@-34.0765258,18.4265338,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x1dcc41e2b6cade59:0x7d001e7f80e9aeb1!8m2!3d-34.0765258!4d18.4287225" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10);">4 Steenberg Road, Steenberg Estate, Tokai, 7945</a></p><p><br /></p><p><strong><u>Cost</u></strong></p><p>Mondays:</p><ul><li>Free Admission</li></ul><p>Wednesdays - Sundays:</p><ul><li>Adults (R160.00)</li><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Under 18's (Free)</span></li></ul><p><strong>Opening hours</strong><br>Monday: 10:00 am – 5:15 pm<br>Tuesday: Closed<br>Wednesday: 8:00 am – 5:15 pm<br>Thursday: 10:00 am – 5:15 pm<br>Friday: 10:00 am – 5:15 pm<br>Saturday: 10:00 am – 7:15 pm<br>Sunday: 10:00 am – 5:15 pm</p>$gb$, $gb$4 Steenberg Rd, Steenberg Estate, Cape Town, 7945, South Africa$gb$, $gb$+27 87 654 5900$gb$, $gb$http://www.norvalfoundation.org/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/5Xf7f6FvRpyqnV4xngkE$gb$, -34.0765258, 18.42872250000005),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-parks-and-nature$gb$, $gb$Parks and Nature$gb$, $gb$Health & Wellness$gb$, $gb$<p><a href="http://www.capetownmagazine.com/de-hel" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Alphen Green Belt</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(31 Alphen Drive, Alphen, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">Approximately a 5km stretch of the most exquisite trail, great for walks and runs.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.grootconstantia.co.za/" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Groot Constantia Estate</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(Groot Constantia Road, Constantia, 7806)</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">The Estate is open to the general public for walking and enjoyment.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><a href="https://www.capetownmagazine.com/de-hel" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Constantia Mountain Hikes</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: black;">If you want to get out and explore the mountain range on foot, there are a couple of moderately easy hikes you can do.</span></p><p><br /></p><p><a href="http://www.gprra.co.za/green-point-urban-park.html" target="_blank" style="color: black;"><strong>Greenpoint Urban Park</strong></a></p><p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">(1 Fritz Sonnenberg Road, Green Point, 8051)</span></p><p>+27 21 444 4258 // <a href="mailto:info@gprra.co.za" target="_blank" style="color: black;">info@gprra.co.za</a></p><p><span style="color: black;">The stadium is home to Green Point Park; a little piece of paradise in the middle of the Mother City. For a fun day out, school tours, family picnics, birthday parties, outdoor exercise, romantic walks, and healthy activities. This is beautiful natural place to get some fresh air and socialise. The carefully curated garden is composed of a rich variety of flora, indigenous to the Cape, and offers the only Biodiversity Showcase Garden of its kind. Go on a journey of self-exploration and get wonderfully lost in the Outdoor Labyrinth, or take a paid tour and discover the world of fynbos.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">*</span><u style="color: black;">Entry is free and picnics are permitted.</u></p><ul><li><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87);">Mondays - Sundays (7:00 a.m. - 7:00 p.m.)</span></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Tokai Forest Walk </strong></p><p>https://www.alltrails.com/ar/trail/south-africa/western-cape/lower-tokai-walk</p><p>Tokai Forest is a stunning area to walk, ride bikes, horse ride and enjoy the fresh air and nature. A new addition not to be missed is The Secret Forest Cafe. Fresh baked croissants, fantastic coffee and breakfasts all served in the beautiful Forest. There is plenty of shade the walk is fairly flat and can be enjoyed by the whole family.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Lions Head </strong></p><p>https://insideguide.co.za/cape-town/things-to-do/lions-head-hike/</p><p>Looming above Cape Town and the surrounding ocean like a sentinel, Lion’s Head is an iconic piece of the city’s wondrous topography. At 669 metres above sea level, its peak offers panoramas of the city, Table Bay and the Atlantic Ocean, making it a wildly popular destination for hiking enthusiasts </p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Ceclila Forest </strong></p><p>https://www.sa-venues.com/attractionswc/cecilia-forest.php</p><p>Cecilia Forest in Cape Town is a beautiful part of Constantia in which to walk. There are a number of routes to choose from, the most popular of which begins at the Cecilia Forest car park where Rhodes and Hohenhort Drives meet.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Newlands Forest </strong></p><p>https://www.alltrails.com/parks/south-africa/western-cape/newlands-forest</p><p>Newlands forest is a gem of Cape Town. Located on the Eastern Slopes of Table Mountain it receives more rainfall than any other part of Cape Town. The result is a spectacular green forest filled with ancient trees, waterfalls, flowers, mushrooms, moss, rivers and ravines!</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Constantia Nek</strong></p><p>https://www.alltrails.com/ar/trail/south-africa/western-cape/constantia-nek-de-villiers-dam-via-jeep-track</p><p>Very straightforward hike that gets you up Table Mountain simply and efficiently on a clearly marked path. Great views over Constantia to False Bay plus really interesting rock formations, fynbos as well as Devilliers Dam at the top.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Silvermine </strong></p><p>https://www.sa-venues.com/game-reserves/silvermine.php</p><p>Located in the central section of the Table Mountain National Park, Silvermine offers some of the best hikes in the Park with beautiful fynbos landscapes.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>$gb$, $gb$Constantia, Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, null, null, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/B2tcCwJ6Qpe42nMoFh9j$gb$, -34.0257608, 18.423078900000064),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-peddlars-bar-and-restaurant$gb$, $gb$Peddlars - Bar and Restaurant$gb$, $gb$bars$gb$, $gb$<p>Peddlars is a favourite destination among both locals and tourists.</p>$gb$, $gb$Spaanschemat River Rd, Brounger Rd, Belle Constantia, Cape Town, 7806, South Africa$gb$, $gb$021 794 7747$gb$, $gb$http://www.peddlars.co.za/$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/osqQOwaJTBCzfVGXPVek$gb$, -34.0299122, 18.4393754),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-personal-trainer$gb$, $gb$Personal Trainer$gb$, $gb$Health & Wellness$gb$, $gb$<p>Personal Trainer - Thomas</p>$gb$, $gb$Cape Town, South Africa$gb$, $gb$+27 73 797 6203$gb$, null, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/rWP5Qc4SjCvVfeWp9v17$gb$, -33.922087, 18.4231418),
  ($gb$montroseterrace-red-bus-cape-town$gb$, $gb$Red Bus - Cape Town$gb$, $gb$activities$gb$, $gb$<p>Great way to see Cape Town. Lots of route options to choose from!</p>$gb$, $gb$Ticket Office, Dock Rd, Victoria & Alfred Waterfront, Cape Town, 8005, South Africa$gb$, $gb$+27 21 511 6000$gb$, $gb$https://www.citysightseeing.co.za/?utm_source=gmb&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=cape-town$gb$, $gb$https://storage.googleapis.com/hostfully-dev-filestack/eyQ6e7PRLGjemgmoQgzU$gb$, -33.907519, 18.417515),
